Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:10.73,Logo,,0000,0000,0000,,TheChaosLegion
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.47,0:00:15.08,English Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,l want to shine on you,\Nand always like that dazzling sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.38,0:00:18.75,English Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,l will defend you\Nfrom all the darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.85,0:00:24.75,English Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the truth from my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.72,0:00:39.53,English Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,lf only our hearts could connect,\Nl could get you to believe me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.63,0:00:46.31,English Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you can't\Nsee it now, don't lose it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.47,0:00:54.25,English Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,Your kindness won't be in vain.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.08,0:01:01.66,English Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be carried aloft by the wind\Nto somewhere that isn't here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.06,0:01:08.76,English Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll cross the sea and cross time,\Nand l know you'll blossom one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.93,0:01:15.40,English Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever the day,\Nl'll be there for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.84,0:01:21.98,English Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,l hope l can watch over you\Nlike the sun for all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.04,0:01:32.02,English Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the truth from my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.65,0:01:32.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(320,136)}Moribito Guardian of the Spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.16,0:01:40.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A double moon?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.47,0:01:48.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Chagum! Run!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.48,0:02:00.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(549,55)}Episode 3
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.48,0:02:00.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(568,324)}Fight \Nto \Nthe \NDeath
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.59,0:02:14.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Chagum, drop what you're carrying\Nand run for the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.80,0:02:20.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.13,0:02:48.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why aren't you using\Nyour blowguns to kill the prince?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.18,0:03:09.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You've switched to a\Ndifferent formation, l see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.48,0:03:12.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you given up on\Ntrying to kill the prince?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.69,0:03:54.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Run into the forest!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.76,0:04:29.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.17,0:04:37.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,l'll go after the woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.54,0:04:40.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Zen, you take Prince Chagum.\NYun, you look after the commander.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.05,0:04:49.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.89,0:04:54.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Unhand me! Let go!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.08,0:05:24.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We got careless.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.79,0:05:29.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,l can't believe that the four of us\Nworking together couldn't kill her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.09,0:05:32.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What of the woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.43,0:05:36.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She is most formidable.\NNot a step since she entered the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.37,0:05:39.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,l'm sure she was slit in the stomach\Nby the commander's sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.90,0:05:42.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Such a wound would compel\Nmost people to flee, but not her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.71,0:05:47.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And she attacked him fully prepared\Nto receive a death blow herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.94,0:05:51.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That she could still charge him\Nknowing she'd be slashed...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.65,0:05:54.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...shows that she has\Nsurvived many battles.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.95,0:05:55.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,True.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.32,0:06:00.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But at the end of the day,\Nshe's just a hired bodyguard.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.05,0:06:01.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,l doubt that she will return.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.12,0:06:04.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How is the commander?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.33,0:06:06.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He'll be fine. He's still breathing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.00,0:06:10.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The rest of you, follow me\Nand carry the commander back.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.80,0:06:13.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We've attained our objective of\Nrecapturing Prince Chagum.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.40,0:06:16.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,l will return with\NHis Highness without delay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.34,0:06:20.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't enter the city. You'll attract\Ntoo much attention looking like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.25,0:06:34.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, looks like we're all right\Nfor the time being.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.29,0:06:38.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My back is stiff as a board...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.70,0:06:42.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, Saya...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.03,0:06:47.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,l think Balsa's mixed up\Nin some ugly business.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.34,0:06:52.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe we should\Ntell Tanda about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.31,0:06:54.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,l think so too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.14,0:06:59.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When Tanda comes to town,\Nhe takes a few days before going home.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.68,0:07:03.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means that he still\Nought to be in town somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.32,0:07:06.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but how do we find him?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.85,0:07:09.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, they don't call me\Nthe best errand runner...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.89,0:07:12.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...in Ogi no Shimo for nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.26,0:07:17.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll just check every inn and\Nrestaurant Tanda might be staying at.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.71,0:07:31.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tanda stops by here every morning\Nand evening to check his orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.78,0:07:37.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,lf there's still this many orders for\NTanda's medicinal herbs, that means...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.29,0:07:40.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...that Tanda hasn't made\Nhis evening pickup yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.15,0:07:42.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So if we wait here...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.56,0:07:44.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...Tanda is sure to come!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.83,0:07:46.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, l see!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.46,0:07:49.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,lf we do it this way, there's\Nno risk of missing him...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.30,0:07:51.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...and we won't have to\Nrun all over town either!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.80,0:07:54.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,l always said that you've got a\Ngood head on your shoulders, Saya!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.96,0:08:25.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's hard to believe that Prince\NChagum has been possessed by...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.17,0:08:26.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...some mysterious water demon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.98,0:08:42.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Can it really only be slain\Nby His Majesty's own sword?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.92,0:09:16.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Were you punished for something?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.59,0:09:17.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your Highness!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.99,0:09:19.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your Highness!\NPrince Chagum!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.89,0:09:26.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, l know! Have this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.56,0:09:27.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your Highness, you mustn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.73,0:09:28.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your Highness, you mustn't!\Nlt's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.37,0:09:36.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?\NDo you not like sweets?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.44,0:09:43.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You needn't be shy.\Nl was given two.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.78,0:09:46.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your Highness...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.62,0:09:49.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,l shall leave it here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.37,0:10:12.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for your\Nkindness, Your Highness!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.67,0:10:15.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,l, Jin, shall never forget it\Nas long as l live!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.88,0:10:23.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,lf l do nothing and bring\NPrince Chagum back...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.09,0:10:27.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...His Majesty will be forced to\Nslay his son by his own hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.56,0:10:32.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Such a terrible thing\Nought not be allowed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.13,0:10:36.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,lf l were to do it myself\Nand sully my own hands here...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.23,0:10:41.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...Prince Chagum would at least be\Nspared death at his father's hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.20,0:10:46.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,l will most certainly be\Nsentenced to death for the deed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.67,0:10:50.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,To lose my life for you would be\Nmy long-cherished ambition!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.02,0:11:04.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Prince Chagum, please forgive\Nthe outrage l am about to commit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.63,0:11:09.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But know that everything l do\Nis for the greater good of Shin-Yogo!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.03,0:11:12.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your faithful servant Jin\Nwill join you immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.98,0:12:07.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(321,42)}Moribito Guardian of the Spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.13,0:12:16.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What on earth is keeping Tanda?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.97,0:12:22.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Saya, l'm gonna go\Nlook around over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.10,0:12:24.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just sitting around waiting\Nisn't getting us anywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.87,0:12:26.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.14,0:12:29.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,l want you to stay here, Saya.\NWe can't afford to miss him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.53,0:12:47.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.33,0:12:54.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa, it is all right.\Nl am able to walk on my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.34,0:13:00.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa? Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.52,0:13:13.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's a sad day when a bodyguard\Nhas her charge worrying over her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.06,0:13:19.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,First, l have to think of a way\Nto keep you safe on your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.93,0:13:22.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep me safe alone?\NWhat do you mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.50,0:13:30.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,To save myself,\Nl have to save you first.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.71,0:13:34.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You shouldn't have to\Nworry needlessly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.98,0:13:41.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Pay close attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.92,0:13:44.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,lf you continue straight down this path...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.29,0:13:48.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...you will see a line of rocks\Nin the shape of a giant bear's back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.42,0:13:55.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,An animal trail is behind it. Follow it,\Nand you will come to a meadow.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.76,0:13:59.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A man named Tanda lives there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.43,0:14:04.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Explain the situation to him\Nand ask him for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.55,0:14:18.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Chagum, when you reach the rock,\Nclimb up and walk along the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.79,0:14:22.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll see the forest\Nbelow you along the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.99,0:14:25.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You might be afraid, but bear with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.76,0:14:32.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The moss will be slippery,\Nso be careful and walk slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.23,0:14:38.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Near the end of the bear's back,\Nclimb down to the meadow.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.17,0:14:44.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,lt will look empty at first, but as\Nyou get closer, you will see a hut.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.81,0:14:48.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,lf everything's clear...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.55,0:14:52.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...then hurry and be on your way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.62,0:14:57.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa? Balsa!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.67,0:15:16.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't climb off the bear's back\Nbefore you reach the end...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.61,0:15:21.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A rock like a bear's back...\NA rock like a bear's back...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.96,0:15:30.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This must be it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.07,0:16:17.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.37,0:16:19.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're sure he went\Nto the health springs?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.81,0:16:20.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.91,0:16:22.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,l better hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.56,0:16:38.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She said that an\Nanimal trail lies beyond.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.02,0:17:02.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is impossible...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.22,0:17:06.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,l think l'll go from down here after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.04,0:17:23.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There are wolves!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.32,0:18:55.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,lf l lose any more blood,\Nl'll be in trouble...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.76,0:18:59.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate, l'll be dead before sunrise.\NNo question about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.74,0:19:06.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When l left, l boasted that l would\Nsave the souls of eight people...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.84,0:19:10.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And now that l have\Nfinally returned, look at me...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.85,0:19:23.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,l knew that l would find you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.97,0:19:34.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Saya! Saya!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.80,0:19:36.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,l found him!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.14,0:19:39.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The old man at the inn said that\NTanda's at the health springs!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.70,0:20:09.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no hut here!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.76,0:20:35.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone! Help me! Somebody!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.90,0:20:42.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.14,0:20:47.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What in the world\Nare you doing out here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.11,0:20:52.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A-Are you Tanda?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.15,0:20:54.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.82,0:20:58.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.32,0:21:01.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,l was in town until recently...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.15,0:21:04.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...but l had so many orders today\Nthat l ran out of medicinal herbs.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.73,0:21:06.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,l only returned just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.63,0:21:09.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you come here after\Nseeing the note l left?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.93,0:21:12.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,lt must have been difficult\Nto come all this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.87,0:21:17.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,For now, come inside and dry yourself.\NWe can talk afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.34,0:21:21.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.68,0:21:25.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's Balsa!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.25,0:22:35.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.86,0:22:54.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.37,0:23:00.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa, are you all right? Hey! Balsa!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.14,0:23:02.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.31,0:23:04.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Balsa!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.71,0:23:13.02,English Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,As l sat huddled and alone, holding\Nback the tears on those nights...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.05,0:23:20.16,English Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,When it felt like l was about\Nto succumb to my doubts...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.19,0:23:25.43,English Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,...there you were,\Nat my side before l knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.47,0:23:32.77,English Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,lt was none other than you\Nwho was there for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.81,0:23:47.05,English Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,l keep wishing, "l want to be strong."\Nl stumble and hurt myself again.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.09,0:23:56.43,English Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,But because l have you to believe in,\Nl can get back to my feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.46,0:24:03.20,English Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,l simply want to tell\Nmy dear one, "Thank you."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.24,0:24:08.34,English Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,At the top of my lungs,\Nagain and again.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.38,0:24:16.72,English Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,l call out to my precious loved one.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.75,0:24:20.92,English Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,ls my voice reaching you?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.95,0:24:29.13,English Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,ln this world that always changes,\Nhuman warmth never does.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.20,0:24:39.51,English Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,l'm certain l sensed the presence\Nof the one that l hold dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.48,0:24:45.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(134,46)}Next Time
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.48,0:24:45.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A wounded woman\Nand a man who heals.
